        "Dawat E Islami USA Inc exhibits a rare financial profile where <cite id=\"4\">total program expenses equal total functional expenses</cite>, suggesting that administrative and fundraising costs are covered through other means or are non-existent in the US entity's reporting. This allows for a <cite id=\"11\">cost per beneficiary of approximately $3.75</cite>, which is considered exceptional for the religious and cultural sector. Furthermore, the organization has demonstrated steady growth with a <cite id=\"12\">3-year revenue CAGR of 5.4%</cite>, indicating sustainable community support over time."
      ],
      "summary": "Dawat E Islami USA Inc is a religious and educational non-profit that reported <cite id=\"1\">total revenue of $2,429,214</cite> in its most recent fiscal year. Founded in <cite id=\"2\">1981</cite>, the organization operates a global network of services focused on spiritual development and community support. Its core programs include <cite id=\"3\">Dar ul Madina, Hifz Quran & Nazra, and Aalim Courses</cite>, which are designed to provide comprehensive Islamic education. The organization demonstrates an exceptional commitment to direct program funding, maintaining a <cite id=\"4\">program expense ratio of 96.4%</cite> according to its latest financial filings. This lean operational model is further evidenced by its <cite id=\"5\">fundraising efficiency of $0.00 spent per $1 raised</cite>, ensuring that donor contributions are utilized almost entirely for service delivery. Beyond education, the charity facilitates religious observances, such as managing <cite id=\"6\">29 I'tikaf locations in Pakistan</cite> and publishing educational materials like <cite id=\"7\">'The Adornment of Ramadan al-Karim'</cite>. With <cite id=\"8\">20.2 months of working capital</cite> in reserve, the organization maintains a strong liquidity position to sustain its international reach across countries including the <cite id=\"9\">USA, UK, Australia, and Bangladesh</cite>.",
